OL,3,CBotched surgical tourism can cost NHS
OL,4,Cnearly #20,000 per patient, study finds
OL,6,FCosmetic and obesity surgery abroad is
OL,7,Fcosting the NHS nearly #20,000 per
OL,8,Fpatient when things go wrong, analysis
OL,9,Fsuggests.
OL,11,FA review of surgical tourism found
OL,12,Fpeople can spend several weeks in NHS
OL,13,Fhospitals when they return home from
OL,14,Fhaving procedures such as bariatric
OL,15,Fsurgery for obesity, tummy tucks and
OL,16,Fbreast enlargement.
OL,18,FComplications treated by the NHS
OL,19,Finclude infected wounds, with some
OL,20,Fpeople needing intensive care and
OL,21,Fprolonged use of antibiotics.
