OL,6,FHe said his "strong advice" to British
OL,7,Ftravellers seeking Brazilian butt
OL,8,Flifts, tummy tucks and other cosmetic
OL,9,Ftreatments was to think carefully
OL,10,Fbefore taking up offers that are "too
OL,11,Fgood to be true".
OL,13,FAsked whether the NHS should be
OL,14,Fpicking up the pieces when things go
OL,15,Fwrong, he said: "We're never going to
OL,16,Fturn people away who are in need of
OL,17,Fcare but this is another pressure the
OL,18,FNHS doesn't need.
